President Barack Obama has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key administration posts. These include Alexander A. Arvizu as Ambassador to the Republic of Albania, Nisha Desai Biswal as Assistant Administrator for Asia at the United States Agency for International Development, Michele T. Bond as Ambassador to the Kingdom of Lesotho, Paul W. Jones as Ambassador to Malaysia, George A. Krol as Ambassador to the Republic of Uzbekistan, Francis J. Ricciardone as Ambassador to the Republic of Turkey, Timothy Charles Scheve as a Member of the Internal Revenue Service Oversight Board, and Duane E. Woerth for the rank of Ambassador during his tenure of service as U.S. Representative on the Council of the International Civil Aviation Organization. President Obama also announced his intent to appoint James M. Kesteloot as a Member of the Committee for Purchase from People Who are Blind or Severely Disabled, Wayne Newell as a Member of the National Advisory Council on Indian Education, Stacy Phelps as a Member of the National Advisory Council on Indian Education, and Patricia Whitefoot as a Member of the National Advisory Council on Indian Education.